{
      "answer": "A reporting policy should uphold integrity, accountability and transparency in its financial strategies. Reporting policy decisions should reflect honesty regarding the firm's net profit, ensuring financial stability, meeting investor expectations and safeguarding against the potential threat of legal repercussions or investor mistrust due to manipulation practices. In this context, considerations like stakeholder protection and fiduciary duty also become crucial aspects in crafting an ethical reporting policy."
   }

